## 8. API Architecture & Execution flow

All Python automation scripts are executed from Node.js routes via the helper module [pythonExecutor.js](file:///d:/College%20Project/CO/backend/utils/pythonExecutor.js).

```text
HTTP Route Request (Node)
        ↓
Validate User ownership and file existence
        ↓
Instantiate Child Process (spawn python candidate)
        ↓
Serialize options arguments as a JSON string
        ↓
Pipe JSON string directly via command-line arguments to script
        ↓
Monitor STDOUT (collect JSON payload) & STDERR (collect errors)
        ↓
Parse STDOUT JSON → Resolve/Reject Promise
```

